@desc
As you approach the corner of Tucker and Locust Avenue, you notice that the pizzeria has been 

remodeled to have no windows.  This was likely the work of scavengers and looters during the early

hours of the virus spreading.  Many businesses and homes were complete ransacked and destroyed

once the shit really hit the fan and families were eating their neighbors. Inside the pizzeria

it is completely dark, however there may be something worthwhile in there if you can brave the 

darkness to try and find it.  As you take in your surroundings you think you hear the shuffle

of feet off in the distance to the north.
#
@open south;s = dtstl1
#
@set here/decor_object = { 'Pile of corpses': 'A medium sized pile of dead bodies, all will bullet holes in the head.  The smell is a mixture of decay, blood and decomposition.' }
#
