@desc
You stick to the shadows as you slowly make your way down Tucker Avenue; what used to be a main roadway

before the infection hit.  The silence is so sustinct that every move you make seems to echo throughout

the entire city and all of its twisting steel and concrete.  The stench of death is gripping your senses

more strongly the closer you make it to the old Courthouse.  You notice the shambling silohuettes of the 

walking dead milling about in the courtyard area of the Courthouse.  Down the road to the south further

you can make out the old police department.  It seems like there is smoke coming out of the building.
