@desc
Continuing down Tucker Avenue you notice a make shift barricade at the following intersection. It's made

from the rusting burned out carcasses of cars and buses.  It has recently been put in place from what you

tell.  It seems that someone, somewhere is still surviving and perhaps trying to thrive.  As you look towards

the Police Department building, you see that what you thought was smoke is really just exhaust from an active

heating unit.  Someone is assuredly in there, and they have...electricity.
